longer than I expected.

95
00:13:49,609 --> 00:13:51,543
So, you're still alive...

96
00:13:53,079 --> 00:13:55,513
The lost Third...

97
00:13:56,716 --> 00:14:00,277
The Angel of
Death and Life, eh ?

98
00:14:21,207 --> 00:14:23,505
Hm ? Oh, hi, Kevin.

99
00:14:23,543 --> 00:14:26,512
You're relieved. Anything
left for me to worry about ?

100
00:14:26,546 --> 00:14:28,946
- Not a damned thing.
- What's that ?

101
00:14:30,483 --> 00:14:35,216
Someone mailed in a threat.
Earth-lovers, most likely.

102
00:14:35,254 --> 00:14:37,484
They apparently
don't like the fact...

103
00:14:37,523 --> 00:14:40,526
...that we make high-compression
propellant here.

104
00:14:40,526 --> 00:14:43,290
They say Martians should
live in the deserts...

105
00:14:43,329 --> 00:14:45,263
...and stop wishing for oceans.

106
00:14:45,298 --> 00:14:47,232
Well, have a nice shift.

107
00:14:59,812 --> 00:15:02,645
All set... Good luck !

108
00:15:33,246 --> 00:15:34,270
Shit !

109
00:15:51,931 --> 00:15:55,492
You aren't going to break through
the security here ! Give up !

110
00:15:55,534 --> 00:15:58,697
Oh, we'll head straight home
after we blow up this facility...

111
00:15:58,738 --> 00:16:00,296
...and all the rocket fuel here !

112
00:16:07,013 --> 00:16:09,140
Come on ! Come on !
ls that all you've got ?!

113
00:16:21,027 --> 00:16:22,392
Shit !

114
00:16:24,397 --> 00:16:26,331
GOOD NIGHT, BABY !

115
00:16:48,321 --> 00:16:50,312
How are you ? Hurt bad ?

116
00:16:50,856 --> 00:16:52,847
Nah, it's nothing serious.

117
00:16:52,892 --> 00:16:56,658
Good to hear. Man, you did
a great job in there.

118
00:16:56,696 --> 00:16:58,823
Outstanding, really.

119
00:16:59,965 --> 00:17:02,729
Unfortunately, there are
some complications...

120
00:17:03,302 --> 00:17:04,269
