121
00:17:05,905 --> 00:17:08,931
The police have just
issued a statement.

122
00:17:09,709 --> 00:17:13,042
They stopped the vehicle
with the escaping terrorists...

123
00:17:13,079 --> 00:17:15,877
...and arrested the last three.

124
00:17:16,182 --> 00:17:20,084
It's just... The three of
them are all robots.

125
00:17:20,119 --> 00:17:23,555
Robots ?! But, what about
the ones I killed ?

126
00:17:23,589 --> 00:17:25,318
They were human.

127
00:17:25,358 --> 00:17:27,121
Humans... ?!

128
00:17:27,560 --> 00:17:30,028
But there was no way I
could tell in that situation !

129
00:17:30,062 --> 00:17:31,893
I know, I know.

130
00:17:31,931 --> 00:17:34,491
We'll have lawyers at
the press conference.

131
00:17:34,533 --> 00:17:37,058
The only words you'll say
are " No comment."

132
00:17:37,103 --> 00:17:39,663
Got that ? Everything will
be fine, so don't worry.

133
00:17:40,539 --> 00:17:43,030
And dress those bandages
up to make it look worse.

134
00:17:43,075 --> 00:17:45,669
You're a hero who risked
his life in the line of duty.

135
00:17:45,711 --> 00:17:49,511
A victim. Got that ?!
Okay, come on !

136
00:18:01,293 --> 00:18:03,227
Hi, Julian.

137
00:18:05,431 --> 00:18:06,989
Hi, Armitage.

138
00:18:07,066 --> 00:18:10,467
It's been a long time since
anyone's called me by that name.

139
00:18:10,503 --> 00:18:11,731
You saw it, right ?

140
00:18:11,771 --> 00:18:14,740
Yeah. You mean about
the First Error, right ?

141
00:18:14,907 --> 00:18:17,273
- Tell me about it.
- It doesn't interest me.

142
00:18:17,309 --> 00:18:19,869
- Why not ?
- Because I'm a ghost.

143
00:18:19,912 --> 00:18:22,073
I couldn't care less about
things in the mortal world.

144
00:18:22,114 --> 00:18:23,775
Julian !

145
00:18:27,386 --> 00:18:28,978
Thanks, Julian.

146
00:18:31,157 --> 00:18:32,886
Judging from the situation...

147
00:18:32,925 --> 00:18:37,328
...M. Kevin Oldman merely
carried out his duty, that's all.

148
00:18:37,663 --> 00:18:40,029
But the three human
terrorists are dead...

149
00:18:40,065 --> 00:18:43,557
... while their three robot
accomplices are completely unharmed.

150
00:18:43,602 --> 00:18:46,298
Is their a special reason
for that, M. Oldman ?

151
00:18:46,372 --> 00:18:49,535
I believe we explained
that already !

152
00:18:49,575 --> 00:18:51,042
When you have
terrorists who are...

153
00:18:51,076 --> 00:18:53,476
...ready to use a liquid
explosive bomb, breaking in...

154
00:18:53,512 --> 00:18:55,707
...do you think
there's time to sort out...

155
00:18:55,748 --> 00:18:57,477
...which are human and
which are robots ?!

156
00:18:57,516 --> 00:19:01,748
The question was for Kevin.
Please answer it, sir.

157
00:19:02,455 --> 00:19:06,084
He's been through enough today !
Would you cut it out already ?

158
00:19:06,459 --> 00:19:07,892
Hold it ! Just a moment !

159
00:19:09,962 --> 00:19:12,453
Are you one of those
robot fetishists ?

160
00:19:12,498 --> 00:19:14,489
Do you subscribe to
"Deep Robo" magazine ?

161
00:19:14,533 --> 00:19:16,402
Do you use a robot maid ?

162
00:19:16,402 --> 00:19:18,393
Ever had sex with a robot ?

163
00:19:18,437 --> 00:19:20,166
Would you all stop it ?!

164
00:19:20,206 --> 00:19:22,538
Robots only do what
they're ordered to do !

165
00:19:22,808 --> 00:19:24,435
The real criminals
are the humans !

166
00:19:29,281 --> 00:19:32,250
...and M. Oldman has gained
an amazing amount of support...

167
00:19:32,284 --> 00:19:35,219
...as the vanguard of those
who believe in Robot Rights...

168
00:19:35,254 --> 00:19:38,951
...and desire a new social order
which denies human supremacy.

169
00:19:38,991 --> 00:19:42,427
Furthermore, the incident is
expected to have a large effect...

170
00:19:42,461 --> 00:19:46,232
...on the upcoming Chicago Summit
between Earth and Mars in 2 weeks...

171
00:19:46,232 --> 00:19:48,427
... which will address
the Robot Rights bill.

172
00:19:48,467 --> 00:19:50,697
We have an analyst
here with an opinion.

173
00:19:50,736 --> 00:19:54,331
Should robots be granted
the same rights as humans ?

174
00:19:54,373 --> 00:19:56,432
Most of Earth has been
against it and would say no...

175
00:19:56,475 --> 00:19:58,670
...but the more liberal
Martians had favored it.

176
00:19:58,711 --> 00:20:02,010
Because of that, the bill was
expected to go nowhere...

177
00:20:02,047 --> 00:20:04,208
...but the aftermath
of the Fist Error...

178
00:20:04,250 --> 00:20:06,878
...slightly moved Martian
public opinion against it.

179
00:20:06,919 --> 00:20:12,323
However, this latest incident has
vitalized Robot Rights activities.

180
00:20:13,459 --> 00:20:15,427
Well, our focus
now will be on...

181
00:20:15,461 --> 00:20:18,123
...how this all affects
the upcoming summit.

182
00:20:23,135 --> 00:20:27,868
You really did it this time, Kevin.
Or should I say Ross Sylibus ?

183
00:20:34,079 --> 00:20:38,812
I'm sorry, all of the robot
doormen were let go.

184
00:20:38,884 --> 00:20:40,613
Let me get that
bag for you.

185
00:21:07,846 --> 00:21:09,780
Who are you ?

186
00:21:10,749 --> 00:21:12,580
You're Strings, right ?

187
00:21:12,618 --> 00:21:15,382
I came to ask why
you killed those robots.

188
00:21:15,421 --> 00:21:16,786
What ?

189
00:21:16,822 --> 00:21:19,725
I'm talking about all
those robots you killed.

190
00:21:19,725 --> 00:21:23,718
Killed ? Robots ?
Don't you mean "destroyed ?"

191
00:21:23,762 --> 00:21:25,389
Does that include
the humans, too ?

192
00:21:25,431 --> 00:21:28,992
You probably know that 18% of
that plant's staff was human.

193
00:21:30,536 --> 00:21:32,902
You act as though you
were there yourself.

194
00:21:34,807 --> 00:21:38,402
For the sake of humanity, for the
sake of our righteous goal...

195
00:21:40,045 --> 00:21:42,878
You... ! You're a robot ?!

196
00:21:49,388 --> 00:21:51,151
You're garbage !

197
00:21:51,190 --> 00:21:53,249
Some sick monster
who gets off on killing !

198
00:21:53,425 --> 00:21:57,191
You killed them all to hide the existence
of the Third Project, didn't you ?!

199
00:21:57,696 --> 00:21:59,994
Third ? What are
you talking about ?

200
00:22:00,032 --> 00:22:01,567
Don't play dumb !

201
00:22:01,567 --> 00:22:03,034
Hold it !

202
00:22:04,103 --> 00:22:07,072
Hold it right there,
Naomi Armitage.

203
00:22:07,673 --> 00:22:09,163
Demitrio...

204
00:22:09,441 --> 00:22:12,035
I can just see
tomorrow's headlines:

205
00:22:12,077 --> 00:22:16,571
" Hero of the First Error suppression,
murdered by robot assassin."

206
00:22:17,049 --> 00:22:18,516
What ?!

207
00:22:44,443 --> 00:22:47,105
Sorry to have exposed you
to such unpleasantness.

208
00:22:47,146 --> 00:22:49,410
How do you
know my name ?

209
00:22:50,215 --> 00:22:52,206
Well, well, well !

210
00:22:52,251 --> 00:22:55,914
Has life on the run dulled
your detective's intuition ?

211
00:22:56,388 --> 00:22:59,357
My name is Demitrio Mardini.

212
00:22:59,391 --> 00:23:02,451
Executive Vice President
of Earth Robotronics.

213
00:23:03,262 --> 00:23:07,358
And you're the daughter of the great
genius, Dr. Asakura, are you not ?

214
00:23:10,035 --> 00:23:14,301
I've been looking forward to
meet you. This is an honor.

215
00:23:14,339 --> 00:23:16,273
Welcome to Earth, my dear !

216
00:23:16,308 --> 00:23:19,038
Now, shall we get
down to business ?

217
00:23:29,988 --> 00:23:31,717
I've brought him, sir.

218
00:23:34,960 --> 00:23:38,259
It's been a long time,
Ross Sylibus.

219
00:23:39,665 --> 00:23:41,155
Mr. Chairman...

220
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:46,934
I called you here for a reason.
I need a favor, Ross.

221
00:23:47,106 --> 00:23:48,596
Y- Yes, sir...

222
00:23:48,874 --> 00:23:51,308
Would you go
to Earth, please ?

223
00:23:51,343 --> 00:23:54,403
I want you to attend
the Chicago Summit.

224
00:23:56,582 --> 00:24:01,212
As the representative
of me, Frederick Ohara...

225
00:24:01,253 --> 00:24:04,586
...chairman of the Martian
Development Foundation.

226
00:24:05,457 --> 00:24:07,652
You'll go, won't you ?

227
00:24:08,560 --> 00:24:10,755
Me, sir...?

228
00:24:13,799 --> 00:24:16,597
To begin with,
the remarkable advancements...

229
00:24:16,635 --> 00:24:21,072
...in robot production techniques on
Mars have been driven by necessity.

230
00:24:21,106 --> 00:24:23,336
The birth rate has been
dropping dramatically...

231
00:24:23,375 --> 00:24:25,309
...since the fourth
generation of colonists.

232
00:24:25,344 --> 00:24:27,212
And there's a labor shortage.

233
00:24:27,212 --> 00:24:32,343
That, in turn, led to a need for
robots to be dependable partners.

234
00:24:33,852 --> 00:24:37,083
If they're to be partners,
they need to be given rights...

235
00:24:37,122 --> 00:24:40,148
...protected by law as good
citizens and good neighbours.

236
00:24:40,192 --> 00:24:43,650
It's the only logical
outcome, isn't it ?

237
00:24:44,863 --> 00:24:47,388
But it's an outcome
I can't allow.

238
00:24:49,601 --> 00:24:52,502
Demand for the Seconds
imported from Mars...

239
00:24:52,538 --> 00:24:54,472
...is slowing my company down.

240
00:24:54,506 --> 00:24:57,771
And if the Robot Rights bill goes
through, things will get worse.

241
00:24:57,810 --> 00:25:01,678
It could shake every union
to its foundations.

242
00:25:01,914 --> 00:25:05,816
As a businessman,
I want to prevent that.

243
00:25:05,851 --> 00:25:08,479
So, you're spinning
a new scenario.

244
00:25:08,520 --> 00:25:11,455
You made up the First Error,
the robot uprising.

245
00:25:12,157 --> 00:25:16,355
Not quite. The uprising
did actually happen.

246
00:25:19,364 --> 00:25:23,232
If you made it all the
way to Earth like this...

247
00:25:23,268 --> 00:25:25,236
...you must know
about that already.

248
00:25:25,270 --> 00:25:28,034
I don't just know
about it ! I saw it !

249
00:25:28,073 --> 00:25:32,009
I'm carrying the memories of a
Third who was built in that plant !

250
00:25:32,945 --> 00:25:37,473
I see. It's fascinating how
you robots communicate...

251
00:25:37,916 --> 00:25:42,216
Listen to me. You Thirds live
a very sad existence.

252
00:25:42,688 --> 00:25:46,647
No one will acknowledge you exist,
and so you're doomed to be forgotten.

253
00:25:46,692 --> 00:25:50,423
What I want is to give you all a
clear and specific purpose in life :

254
00:25:50,863 --> 00:25:53,627
The creation of human beings !

255
00:25:53,665 --> 00:25:55,496
A most honorable
purpose, is it not ?

256
00:25:56,201 --> 00:25:59,136
Oh, that's bullshit ! Why do
you think the Thirds rebelled...

257
00:25:59,171 --> 00:26:01,298
...when they were forced
into that research ?!

258
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:03,965
Well, I can't believe it.

259
00:26:04,309 --> 00:26:09,110
Your friends tried to escape
from the Garden of Eden.

260
00:26:10,282 --> 00:26:13,718
Listen, this is a wonderful
operation I'm proposing.

261
00:26:14,620 --> 00:26:17,453
From time immemorial, the most
difficult task has been...

262
00:26:17,489 --> 00:26:19,923
...the creation of humans
you can manipulate freely.

263
00:26:21,026 --> 00:26:23,324
Now you can do it.

264
00:26:23,362 --> 00:26:25,853
You can make a cheap labor
force who will never complain.

265
00:26:25,898 --> 00:26:27,832
Or produce soldiers
who aren't afraid of dying.

266
00:26:27,866 --> 00:26:29,993
Creating people to simply love
would be nice, too, wouldn't it ?

267
00:26:30,035 --> 00:26:32,697
The ultimate product,
wouldn't you say ?

268
00:26:33,538 --> 00:26:36,837
You...
You want to play God ?

269
00:26:39,077 --> 00:26:40,669
Not quite...

270
00:26:40,879 --> 00:26:44,337
Perhaps just have the
power of one of His chosen.

271
00:26:44,383 --> 00:26:47,784
And that's why you killed the
human staff members as well.

272
00:26:47,819 --> 00:26:49,787
Yes, that's right.

273
00:26:52,391 --> 00:26:56,061
So, won't you come with me ?
To my Garden of Eden ?

274
00:26:56,061 --> 00:26:59,929
If you have that other Third's
memories, you must understand.

275
00:26:59,965 --> 00:27:02,866
I need your power.
I need you...

276
00:27:02,901 --> 00:27:05,893
The original Third.

277
00:27:06,571 --> 00:27:08,173
Go to hell.

278
00:27:08,173 --> 00:27:10,038
You disappoint me.

279
00:27:16,615 --> 00:27:17,411
Grab her !

280
00:27:20,152 --> 00:27:22,279
You seem to be in pain
all of a sudden.

281
00:27:34,566 --> 00:27:37,467
So, how do you like
its jamming functions ?

282
00:27:48,347 --> 00:27:49,871
All right ! Take her !

283
00:27:54,753 --> 00:27:56,516
What's wrong ?!

284
00:28:01,626 --> 00:28:04,424
This date's over.
You're just not my type !

285
00:28:29,354 --> 00:28:32,858
Did she get away ?
Or is she dead ?

286
00:28:32,858 --> 00:28:35,258
No...
She's a Third, after all...

287
00:29:41,259 --> 00:29:44,023
Oh, I found a
real beauty here !

288
00:29:44,062 --> 00:29:47,395
This isn't some consumer model you
can get off the assembly lines !

289
00:29:47,432 --> 00:29:50,458
Skeletal frame says
" Made on Mars."

290
00:29:51,803 --> 00:29:55,034
Well, let's ask this little
stranger who she is...

291
00:29:58,310 --> 00:30:01,006
These are her
latest memories.

292
00:30:03,415 --> 00:30:06,316
I doubt it misfired...

293
00:30:08,353 --> 00:30:10,116
Oh, I see...

294
00:30:10,155 --> 00:30:13,147
She took over its power systems
and then must have activated...

295
00:30:13,191 --> 00:30:16,126
...the gun's safety and its
proximity fuse at the same time.

296
00:30:16,161 --> 00:30:19,289
Well, that's how you use
telepresence abilities !

297
00:30:19,664 --> 00:30:21,393
Hey !

298
00:30:21,433 --> 00:30:23,731
Quit poking around
in my memories !

299
00:30:24,703 --> 00:30:26,694
Didn't mean any harm !

300
00:30:26,738 --> 00:30:30,675
I'm Mouse, a repairman.
And you, my dear, are a mess.

301
00:30:30,675 --> 00:30:34,270
Your main autonomous nerve lines and
vital parts are completely severed.

302
00:30:34,312 --> 00:30:36,212
If you went to a dealer...

303
00:30:36,248 --> 00:30:40,116
...they'd tell you to forget about
repairs and just buy a new body !

304
00:30:40,785 --> 00:30:44,243
Unfortunately, I'm kinda
attached to this body.

305
00:30:44,289 --> 00:30:46,883
Anyway, l need to move again.
Can you do that ?

306
00:30:46,925 --> 00:30:50,952
CAN I ? I am a genius !

307
00:30:51,196 --> 00:30:53,630
However, it'll cost you.

308
00:30:53,665 --> 00:30:56,600
Payment to be made in
Earth dollars. And no IOUs !

309
00:31:24,229 --> 00:31:27,255
We will soon be arriving
at the orbital station.

310
00:31:27,299 --> 00:31:30,936
The following connecting shuttles
are scheduled to leave from there:

311
00:31:30,936 --> 00:31:34,167
Chicago, flight 102,
departing at 13:00.

312
00:31:34,206 --> 00:31:35,264
Basilia, flight 347...

313
00:31:35,307 --> 00:31:39,073
Daddy, it's just like
you said ! It's so pretty !

314
00:31:39,110 --> 00:31:41,806
Toonto, flight 618,
departing at 14:10.

315
00:31:41,846 --> 00:31:43,473
Yeah...

316
00:31:44,216 --> 00:31:46,878
Would you go
to Earth, please ?

317
00:31:48,119 --> 00:31:49,643
We've worked so hard on...

318
00:31:49,688 --> 00:31:52,680
...the Robot Rights summit
and have gotten so far.

319
00:31:52,724 --> 00:31:55,887
I naturally intended
to attend it myself...

320
00:31:55,927 --> 00:32:00,125
...but in light of what happened
to you, I've changed my mind.

321
00:32:02,667 --> 00:32:05,397
Earth is very nervous about...

322
00:32:05,437 --> 00:32:08,429
...the rising drive for
Martian independence.

323
00:32:08,473 --> 00:32:10,566
They're threatened
by the pressure for...

324
00:32:10,609 --> 00:32:12,543
...the Zephyria Terra
forming project.

325
00:32:12,577 --> 00:32:14,545
And now they're
telling us to accept...

326
00:32:14,579 --> 00:32:17,343
...40 million immigrants during
the fourth stage of development.

327
00:32:17,382 --> 00:32:19,043
Their attitude is drastic.

328
00:32:19,818 --> 00:32:25,586
The point is, Earth wants to
keep Mars as its colony.

329
00:32:28,960 --> 00:32:33,158
Despite what it says,
we all need robots now.

330
00:32:33,198 --> 00:32:38,226
Not just for Martian development,
but for humanity's future.

331
00:32:38,270 --> 00:32:41,205
And the Rights bill is
necessary for that future.

332
00:32:41,239 --> 00:32:45,266
I agree with you.
But, why me, sir ?

333
00:32:45,310 --> 00:32:48,143
Because you're the
man for the time.

334
00:32:48,613 --> 00:32:50,911
The hero of Mars.

335
00:32:51,449 --> 00:32:57,410
Oh, you may not have intended
to become that, but you are now.

336
00:32:58,089 --> 00:33:01,626
I would like to use your
standing to full advantage...

337
00:33:01,626 --> 00:33:04,356
...in getting the Robot
Rights bill passed.

338
00:33:05,630 --> 00:33:10,635
Ross... You can't keep
hiding forever.

339
00:33:10,635 --> 00:33:15,334
This is also a good chance to
ensure Yoko's future, isn't it ?

340
00:33:17,942 --> 00:33:23,209
Let's say, if you scratch
my back, I'll scatch yours...

341
00:33:24,449 --> 00:33:26,314
Thank you for choosing
All Martian Spacelines today.

342
00:33:26,351 --> 00:33:28,819
What have you
got there, Yoko ?

343
00:33:28,853 --> 00:33:30,753
It's a secret !

344
00:33:32,891 --> 00:33:35,451
I hope we see
Mommy soon...

345
00:33:36,328 --> 00:33:40,230
And with 2 days to go until the
Chicago Summit on Robot Rights opens...

346
00:33:40,265 --> 00:33:43,632
...All Martian Spacelines
flight 102 landed...

347
00:33:43,668 --> 00:33:46,728
... with the Martian
representatives today.

348
00:33:47,305 --> 00:33:51,639
Among them is this man,
currently the talk of the town.

349
00:33:51,676 --> 00:33:53,769
M. Kevin Oldman.

350
00:33:53,812 --> 00:33:55,714
As a result of his comments...

351
00:33:55,714 --> 00:33:58,583
...made after the terrorist attack on
Astro Technologies only days ago...

352
00:33:58,583 --> 00:34:00,752
...he's received overwhelming
support from Robot Rights activists.

353
00:34:00,752 --> 00:34:02,879

354
00:34:27,078 --> 00:34:28,045
Nice job !

355
00:34:42,394 --> 00:34:44,919
Okay, I have a few
little things to do now.

356
00:34:44,963 --> 00:34:47,022
Once I'm done,
we'll go look for Mommy.

357
00:35:12,624 --> 00:35:15,991
Before the opening of today's
summit on Robot Rights...

358
00:35:16,027 --> 00:35:18,860
...all of the major
robotronics companies'..

359
00:35:18,897 --> 00:35:21,457
...sagging stockprices
are now taking off.

360
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:26,232
This is due to their announcement
that all robots will now be made...

361
00:35:26,271 --> 00:35:30,275
... with a slave circuit installed
which will guarantee loyalty...

362
00:35:30,275 --> 00:35:32,937
...and ensure that robots
will never harm humans.

363
00:35:33,244 --> 00:35:35,678
Stockholdes are also reacting
positively to the possibility...

364
00:35:35,713 --> 00:35:38,273
...that the industry's healthy
economy might be restored...

365
00:35:38,316 --> 00:35:40,546
...should the Robot Rights bill
fail to win passage.

366
00:36:12,817 --> 00:36:16,309
Welcome, Mr. Oldman.

367
00:36:16,354 --> 00:36:19,983
What's going on here ?!
Where's my daughter ?!

368
00:36:20,024 --> 00:36:23,790
Please, calm down.
As you can see, she's unharmed.

369
00:36:24,896 --> 00:36:25,885
Yoko !

370
00:36:28,533 --> 00:36:30,635
Why are you doing this ?!

371
00:36:30,635 --> 00:36:33,570
I want you to vote against
the Robot Rights bill.

372
00:36:33,605 --> 00:36:34,936
What ?!

373
00:36:34,973 --> 00:36:37,237
The reason being...
Well...

374
00:36:37,275 --> 00:36:39,743
If I call you this,
will you understand then...

375
00:36:41,946 --> 00:36:43,811
...Ross Sylibus ?

376
00:36:43,848 --> 00:36:45,372
How did you... ?!

377
00:36:49,454 --> 00:36:52,321
You seem to
catch on fast.

378
00:36:52,357 --> 00:36:54,018
If you vote against the bill...

379
00:36:54,058 --> 00:36:57,084
...your pretty little daughter
will be returned unharmed.

380
00:36:57,128 --> 00:37:00,791
If you don't do
as I ask, well...

381
00:37:01,032 --> 00:37:03,762
It's all up to you, isn't it ?

382
00:37:04,369 --> 00:37:05,927
It's now time for the vote...

383
00:37:05,970 --> 00:37:09,030
...at the much anticipated
Chicago Summit on Robot Rights.

384
00:37:09,073 --> 00:37:11,803
Let's now go live
via relay to the summit.

385
00:37:16,381 --> 00:37:17,541
Ross...?

386
00:37:18,182 --> 00:37:19,984
We will begin
taking the vote.

387
00:37:19,984 --> 00:37:22,487
All those in favor of
the new bill from Mars...

388
00:37:22,487 --> 00:37:25,285
...the Robot Rights bill,
please standup.

389
00:37:27,458 --> 00:37:29,358
What's going on ?

390
00:37:30,795 --> 00:37:34,026
As expected, all the Martian
delegates are for the bill...

391
00:37:34,065 --> 00:37:37,159
... while all of the Earth
delegates oppose it.

392
00:37:37,201 --> 00:37:39,396
Once again the Martian
bill will not easily pass--

393
00:37:41,406 --> 00:37:42,566
What's this ?!

394
00:37:42,607 --> 00:37:45,735
M. Oldman, one of the Martian
delegates, isn't standing in support!

395
00:37:45,777 --> 00:37:49,076
If he doesn't stand,
the bill will be thrown out !

396
00:37:49,714 --> 00:37:51,477
He's up ! No, wait !

397
00:37:51,516 --> 00:37:52,414
Ross !

398
00:37:53,251 --> 00:37:55,412
He 's approaching the chairman.

399
00:37:58,089 --> 00:38:02,583
Three votes for passage,
four against, one abstention.

400
00:38:02,627 --> 00:38:04,891
The motion is denied !

401
00:38:05,930 --> 00:38:08,421
M. Oldman has
abstained from the vote !

402
00:38:08,466 --> 00:38:10,525
This is a completely
unexpected turn !

403
00:38:10,568 --> 00:38:12,502
The bill has not passed !

404
00:38:17,442 --> 00:38:21,708
He abstained...
Well, I'll let it go.

405
00:38:59,751 --> 00:39:02,083
What am I missing ?

406
00:39:03,554 --> 00:39:06,682
Or are you telling me
the ability to conceive life...

407
00:39:06,724 --> 00:39:08,817
...is only in the
province of God...?

408
00:39:13,898 --> 00:39:17,197
Hi there, Demitrio !
You want my data ?

409
00:39:17,769 --> 00:39:20,761
Hi there, Demitrio !
You want my data ?

410
00:39:20,805 --> 00:39:22,636
Who's...?

411
00:39:23,775 --> 00:39:25,402
Yes.

412
00:39:25,910 --> 00:39:28,344
Then I'll transfer
some sample data for you.

413
00:39:28,379 --> 00:39:32,372
If you want the merchandise,
contact Mouse Robot Service.

414
00:39:32,583 --> 00:39:34,380
Your password is...

415
00:39:35,653 --> 00:39:38,144
An informant, eh ?
Interesting...

416
00:39:56,340 --> 00:39:57,773
All set.

417
00:39:59,677 --> 00:40:03,841
Please feel free to deal with
Mouse Robot Service any time.

418
00:40:03,881 --> 00:40:06,315
You now have the
last of the data...

419
00:40:06,350 --> 00:40:08,250
Hold it.

420
00:40:08,286 --> 00:40:10,345
Let me confirm this.

421
00:40:19,263 --> 00:40:21,663
So, this is the last
of the data, you say ?

422
00:40:22,467 --> 00:40:25,664
BULLSHIT !
This isn't all of it !

423
00:40:25,703 --> 00:40:30,436
It is, I swear ! What you
wanted is on that disc, too !

424
00:40:33,144 --> 00:40:36,636
What I want is the data
on her ability to conceive !

425
00:40:38,616 --> 00:40:39,984
Wh- What... ?!

426
00:40:39,984 --> 00:40:41,815
Tell me !
Where are you hiding it ?!

427
00:40:41,853 --> 00:40:43,514
I don't know about
any such data !

428
00:40:43,554 --> 00:40:47,115
If it's in there,
it's somewhere out of my reach !

429
00:40:47,158 --> 00:40:49,251
Anyway, I gave you
everything I have !

430
00:40:49,293 --> 00:40:53,127
If you can't analyze it,
your system must be obsolete !

431
00:40:53,164 --> 00:40:54,995
Don't play dumb !
I can't complete...

432
00:40:55,032 --> 00:40:57,432
...the conception functions
with just this data !

433
00:40:59,170 --> 00:41:01,229
That's impossible !

434
00:41:01,272 --> 00:41:04,537
You should be able to clone her
exactly by copying the hardware...

435
00:41:05,076 --> 00:41:07,271
Something must
be wrong, then...!

436
00:41:09,247 --> 00:41:10,646
You...!

437
00:41:14,352 --> 00:41:18,413
You don't have the vital piece ?!
Some informant !

438
00:41:43,014 --> 00:41:45,107
What the...?!

439
00:41:52,456 --> 00:41:54,117
Armitage...?

440
00:42:01,766 --> 00:42:05,429
Just like her, aren't they ?
99% like her, at least.

441
00:42:05,469 --> 00:42:08,461
But I'm still missing
that last, vital part.

442
00:42:09,040 --> 00:42:12,032
Now then, give me
the remaining data.

443
00:42:12,143 --> 00:42:15,169
I told you, I don't have it !

444
00:42:15,213 --> 00:42:18,307
Don't you want to see robots
who can give birth to children ?

445
00:42:18,349 --> 00:42:20,044
Oh, get real !

446
00:42:24,322 --> 00:42:26,552
He must have a
connector somewhere.

447
00:42:27,158 --> 00:42:30,025
Rip the data out
of his memory bank.

448
00:42:51,115 --> 00:42:52,514
Well ?

449
00:42:54,118 --> 00:42:55,983
Shit...

450
00:42:58,155 --> 00:43:01,647
All that leaves us
with is the daughter.

451
00:43:03,027 --> 00:43:05,587
Dump this trash
in the bin, would you ?

452
00:43:21,212 --> 00:43:25,410
That son of a bitch !
I won't forget this !

453
00:43:25,716 --> 00:43:29,345
I swear... He'll regret
messing with me...!

454
00:43:34,392 --> 00:43:36,792
Hotel Royal Greenhill.

455
00:43:36,827 --> 00:43:39,387
The Martian Development
Foundation representatives, please.

456
00:43:39,430 --> 00:43:41,591
Well, they've
gone already...

457
00:43:41,632 --> 00:43:43,759
M. Kevin Oldman, as well ?

458
00:43:43,801 --> 00:43:48,966
No, he isn't back yet, so he's still
registered as staying in this hotel.

459
00:43:49,907 --> 00:43:52,171
Can l help you
with anything else ?

460
00:43:54,011 --> 00:43:57,310
No, nevermind.
Thank you.

461
00:44:01,319 --> 00:44:03,287
What's happened, Ross ?

462
00:44:44,595 --> 00:44:46,495
Sorry to keep you waiting.

463
00:44:47,665 --> 00:44:52,125
Where's my daughter ?!
You promised me you'd return her !

464
00:44:52,636 --> 00:44:56,766
Relax. As promised,
you'll be with your daughter again...

465
00:44:59,143 --> 00:45:00,371
In Heaven.

466
00:45:01,545 --> 00:45:03,479
You were planning this
from the start, weren't you ?!

467
00:45:07,385 --> 00:45:08,784
What the hell...?

468
00:45:08,953 --> 00:45:10,352
Get out !

469
00:45:10,621 --> 00:45:12,714
Who the hell are you ?!

470
00:45:12,757 --> 00:45:14,486
Police officer !

471
00:45:15,092 --> 00:45:16,821
Well, formerly...

472
00:45:34,245 --> 00:45:35,940
Why, you...!

473
00:45:49,827 --> 00:45:51,089
What ?!

474
00:45:52,863 --> 00:45:54,091
These guys are nuts !

475
00:47:51,448 --> 00:47:53,882
The day Yoko was born...

476
00:47:53,918 --> 00:47:58,287
I was so happy. The happiest
I've ever been in my life .

477
00:47:59,557 --> 00:48:02,151
But I was worried, too.

478
00:48:04,361 --> 00:48:08,263
I was worried that, one day,
I might lose both you and Yoko.

479
00:48:14,505 --> 00:48:16,166
I'm sorry.

480
00:48:16,207 --> 00:48:18,402
I'm sorry I left
without telling you.

481
00:48:19,677 --> 00:48:22,942
But I just had to
know the truth.

482
00:48:22,980 --> 00:48:25,244
Because I'm a Third, too.

483
00:48:27,952 --> 00:48:31,513
And now my precious little
Yoko is mixed up in all this.

484
00:48:32,623 --> 00:48:34,921
Some mother I am...!

485
00:48:48,539 --> 00:48:50,370
Naomi...

486
00:48:50,407 --> 00:48:53,240
Stop trying to take on
every problem by yourself.

487
00:48:58,916 --> 00:49:03,387
We can change our names
and forge new identities...

488
00:49:03,387 --> 00:49:06,220
...but if we can't
escape our destiny...

489
00:49:06,257 --> 00:49:08,191
...then we'll fight it.

490
00:49:09,093 --> 00:49:12,824
For Yoko...
And for us as a family.

491
00:49:15,966 --> 00:49:17,558
